<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-07-07T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-07-07T00:00:00-05:00" n="506" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d506">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Gresham</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">McKenzie</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-07-07"><hi rend="italic">July 7,
                            1893</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 9.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have received Mr. Hicks, No. 512, of the
                        17th ultimo, reporting the final settlement of the claim of Enrique Meier,
                        our acting consular agent at Mollendo, by the payment to him for the
                        claimant of 2,000 sols from the Peruvian Government, and am gratified to
                        learn that the settlement was reached in this straightforward and friendly
                        way.</p>
                    <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                    <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">W. Q. Gresham.</hi></signed></closer>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>